KPM (Kapuletu Project Manager)
Product Definition
Version: 1.0
Document Type: Product Definition & Solution Overview

1. Introduction
Overview
KPM (Kapuletu Project Manager) is an integrated engineering project delivery platform designed to manage the complete lifecycle of software projects.
Unlike traditional project management tools that focus primarily on task tracking, KPM provides a structured environment where project planning, documentation, team coordination, sprint management, engineering execution, quality assurance, reviews, approvals, and product delivery operate as one connected system.
KPM serves as the single operational workspace for engineering organizations, ensuring every project progresses through clearly defined stages while maintaining visibility, accountability, quality, and collaboration across all disciplines.
The platform is built around one principle:
Engineering projects should be managed as complete products, not collections of disconnected tasks.

2. Problem Statement
Modern software development is fragmented.
Engineering teams rely on multiple independent platforms to manage a single project.
Typical tools include:
Documentation platforms
Design software
Sprint management systems
Meeting platforms
Source control repositories
Communication tools
QA platforms
Cloud deployment services
Each platform solves one part of the engineering lifecycle but none provide a unified operational workflow.
This fragmentation results in:
Poor coordination between teams
Unclear project ownership
Weak sprint execution
Inconsistent documentation
Dependency bottlenecks
Slow delivery
Lack of visibility
Last-minute rushes
Knowledge loss between projects
Difficulty maintaining engineering standards
Small and growing engineering teams are particularly affected because project managers often spend more time coordinating disconnected tools than delivering software.

3. Solution Statement
KPM provides a unified Engineering Delivery Platform where the entire software development lifecycle is managed within one connected ecosystem.
Instead of separating planning, documentation, development, reviews, meetings, testing, and releases into different tools, KPM integrates them into a structured workflow centered on product delivery.
Every engineering activity is connected to:
the project,
the roadmap,
the feature,
the sprint,
the responsible team,
and the final release.
This enables organizations to maintain complete visibility from project creation through production deployment.

4. Product Vision
To become the operating system for modern software engineering teams by transforming how projects are planned, coordinated, executed, reviewed, and delivered.

5. Product Mission
To provide engineering organizations with one intelligent platform that simplifies collaboration, improves delivery quality, and enables predictable software execution.

6. Core Principles
KPM is built around the following principles:
Build products, not isolated tasks.
Features are the primary unit of delivery.
Documentation should drive execution.
Communication should be structured.
Every decision should be traceable.
Visibility should replace guesswork.
Quality should be integrated into the workflow.
Every project should have a repeatable delivery process.
Teams should collaborate through the system rather than around it.

